summary:
I am in the media industry since 2012 as a freelance audio-visual content producer, lecturer and writer. Sociology and anthropology has always been a passion for me that helps me to uncover the problems in life and provide a solution. This let me to become a lecturer and share knowledge to improve future generations in Near East. 

Moreover, I have started working in MediaLife, a commercial agency where we organized marketing strategies, media contents, event organizations for private companies. We produced original content, created and edited promotional pictures and videos for the top companies like Cratos Hotel - Cage Club, Alpet Gas Station, etc. I also worked in a company named EnModa where my job mainly focused on advertising social accounts; producing promotional materials like photos or videos and creating a marketing strategy for big brands like Iktisat Bank and Remax Golden. 

In addition I have worked in Maastricht University in Content Production and Management, where I've filmed numerous commercials, promotional videos, podcasts and more for the university and the EU. In addition, I do digital marketing and content producing for Unitive Consulting agency situated in USA, California. 

Lastly, I am also a musician for more than 9 years as a vocalist and a guitarist. I usually compose the music that I use for short films, documentaries or promotional contents.
